      "content": "but if the goal is a human right, then the mechanism is secondary, right? it feels like when people argue about the \"efficiency\" part, they're basically just trying to pick an excuse to deny people care. isn't it more accurate to say that the debate is really just between people who prioritize human life and people who prioritize economic efficiency?",
